sub_title: Hardworking Graduate Geologist. I have received 5 merit awards and aided in various geology projects conducted by UWC.
summary:
I am determined to pursue a career in geology. I hold a B.Sc. Honours Applied Geology and I have completed several lectures which make me fit in any specialised field of geology. Five academic merit awards demonstrate my hard-work and dedication. My abilitise and skills include but not limited to:         Self Confidence
 Hard Worker and Can Work Under Pressure
 Can Work as an Individual and in a Group
 Keen to Learn New Challenges 
 Computer Literate (MS Office)
 Research, Report Writing and Presentations Skills
 Can Work Under Minimal Supervision

projects: [{'title': 'Geological mapping and characterization, Robertson Area', 'date': {'start': {'month': 6, 'day': None, 'year': 2014}, 'end': {'month': 11, 'day': None, 'year': 2014}}, 'description': 'Geological mapping, sedimentological analysis and characterization of the Dwyka Group of the Karoo Supergroup and the Witteberg Group of the Cape Supergroup adjacent to the Breede River, Robertson area were conducted. The study area is in the Breede River Valley of the Cape Fold Belt syntaxis in the Robertson Area. The area lies between latitudes S33˚48̍1.44̎ and S33˚48̍53.28̎, and longitudes E019˚38̍16.8̎ and E019˚39̍8.64̍. Newton et al.  (2006) concluded that the Cape Fold Belt is largely ambiguous, for instance, the presence of two orthogonal converging trends, the low grade metamorphism and the apparent lack of significant igneous activity in preserved part of the fold belt pose problems for conventional plate-tectonic explanations and structures are poorly mapped in many areas in the fold belt. For these reasons, the study was carried out to determine the depositional environment, palaeocurrent directions, structural features, deformation and metamorphism, structural and tectonic evolution of the Cape Fold Belt, and of the Witteberg and Dwyka Groups in particular. Results were obtained by traversing, while analyzing and mapping the lithologies of the area.', 'contributors': [{'type': 'standardizedContributor', 'first_name': 'SIPESIHLE LUTHANDO', 'last_name': 'Mncamase (Pr.Sci.Nat.)', 'name': None, 'headline': 'Hardworking Graduate Geologist.
